 <BODY>
  <HEADLINE>
   <S PAR="1" RSNT="1" SNO="1">Chief Executive Received International Visitors</S>
  </HEADLINE>
  <TEXT>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>The Chief Executive, Mr Tung Chee Hwa, met with three visitors who were passing through Hong Kong en route to attend the Handover Ceremony and related events in Macao this afternoon (Saturday).</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>They are the Princess of Thailand, Her Royal Highness Princess Maha Chakri Sirindhorn, the Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of Foreign Affairs of Belgium, Mr Louis Michel, and the European Commissioner in charge of External Relations, Mr Christopher Patten.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The Chief Executive recalled the visit of Her Royal Highness to attend the Handover Ceremony in 1997 and warmly welcomed her visiting Hong Kong again.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>With the Deputy Prime Minister of Belgium, Mr. Tung said that with China's expected accession to the World Trade Organisation, Hong Kong would continue to provide a most important springboard for Belgian companies to invest in the Mainland.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>At the meeting with the European Commissioner, Mr Patten, the Chief Executive noted that EU was our third largest trading partner in the world in 1998.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='2' SNO='7'>Mr. Tung believed that bilateral trade and investment relations would grow even stronger.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The Chief Executive said that Hong Kong had always supported China's accession to WTO.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='2' SNO='9'>This would be important to the Hong Kong economy and we hoped that the European Union would reach agreement with China at an early date.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Turning to increased travel convenience for Hong Kong people, Mr Tung said that a visa-free policy towards HKSAR passport holders would be beneficial to the promotion of trade, economic and tourism ties between Hong Kong and the EU.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='2' SNO='11'>Mr Tung hoped that the European Commission would support granting visa-free access to holders of HKSAR passports.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Photo: The Chief Executive, Mr Tung Chee Hwa, met with the Princess of Thailand, Her Royal Highness Princess Maha Chakri Sirindhorn, the Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of Foreign Affairs of Belgium, Mr Louis Michel, and the European Commissioner in charge of External Relations, Mr Christopher Patten, at separate meetings.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='2' SNO='13'>The three visitors are passing through Hong Kong en route to attend the Handover Ceremony and related events in Macao.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='3' SNO='14'>The Chief Executive, Mr Tung Chee Hwa, photographed with the Belgian Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of Foreign Affairs, Mr Louis Michel, at the Chief Executive's Office after a meeting.</S>
  </TEXT>
